comments.text:
ASTSerializer::literal() contains this code:

        if (!js_GetClassPrototype(cx, &cx->fp()->scopeChain(), JSProto_RegExp, &proto))
            return false;

The scope-chain bit is wrong, I believe, if the stack has no script running.  This could be the case if Reflect.parse were called via setTimeout.  At present I think the right thing to do here would be to pass NULL instead (although longer-term this too is wrong, I believe).

